<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Brakes - Anti-Lock Control - 4-Wheel - Removal and Installation</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="14">
        <title>Removal and Installation</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hydraulic Control Unit</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Brake fluid contains polyglycol ethers and polyglycols. Avoid contact with eyes. Wash hands
                        thoroughly after handling. If brake fluid contacts eyes, flush eyes with running water for 15
                        minutes. Get medical attention if irritation persists. If taken internally, drink water and
                        induce vomiting. Get medical attention immediately. Failure to follow these instructions may
                        result in personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Electronic modules are sensitive to static electrical charges. If exposed to these charges,
                        damage may result.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Brake fluid is harmful to painted and plastic surfaces. If brake fluid is spilled onto a
                        painted or plastic surface, immediately wash it with water.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Only authorized inlet hydraulic brake tubes should be used. These tubes are of specific design
                        and only authorized parts should be used when installing new inlet brake tubes.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When installing either the HCU or the anti-lock brake system (ABS) module individually, make
                        sure that the number of coils (metal cans) in the ABS module equals the number of valves in the
                        HCU. This is an additional method of verifying that the correct replacement part number has been
                        selected.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S08/S08307.htm" bookname="S08307">Battery, Mounting and Cables in
                        S08307</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push the lock forward and release the ABS electrical connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0009375.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Plug each open port to prevent brake fluid from spilling.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the hydraulic brake line fittings.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>To install, tighten the 1/2-20 fittings to 25 Nm (18 lb-ft).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>To install, tighten the 7/16-24 fittings to 17 Nm (13 lb-ft).</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the nut and remove the fuel lines from bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609008" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0028711.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nuts and the HCU and bracket assembly.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 30 Nm (22 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609009" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0028710.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolt and remove the HCU from the bracket.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 11 Nm (8 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609010" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0028724.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure. Bleed the brake system. For additional
                    information, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s04049_X2060015.xml" xrefid="x2060015">Brake System</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Anti-Lock Brake System (ABS) Module</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When installing a new HCU or anti-lock brake system (ABS) module individually, make sure that
                        the number of coils (metal cans) in the ABS module equals the number of valves in the HCU. This
                        is an additional method of verifying that the correct replacement part number has been selected.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S08/S08307.htm" bookname="S08307">Battery, Mounting and Cables in
                        S08307</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push the lock forward and release the ABS electrical connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0009375.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the screws and the ABS module.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 3 Nm (27 lb-in).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609013" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0028725.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Verify correct ABS operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Rear Wheel Speed Sensor</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S08/S08307.htm" bookname="S08307">Battery, Cables and Mounting in
                        S08307</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise and support the vehicle. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S10/S10019.htm" bookname="S10019">Jacking and Lifting in S10019</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the rear wheel speed sensor.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove the bolt.</para>
                        <randlist type="dash">
                            <item>
                                <para>To install, tighten to 20 Nm (15 lb-ft).</para>
                            </item>
                        </randlist>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove the rear wheel speed sensor.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609014" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0028722.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use care not to get dirt in the rear axle housing.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
                <para>Clean and inspect the rear anti-lock brake sensor.</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Clean the axle mounting surface.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Inspect and clean the magnetized rear anti-lock brake sensor pole piece.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Inspect the rear anti-lock brake sensor O-ring for damage. Install a new O-ring if
                        necessary.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the rear anti-lock brake sensor O-ring rear axle lubricant.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Front Wheel Speed Sensor</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the front anti-lock brake sensor electrical connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609015" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figGH1/GH1018A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Separate the sensor cable from the brake hose clips.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609016" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figGH1/GH1019A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the front anti-lock brake sensor bolt and the front anti-lock brake sensor.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 18 Nm (13 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609017" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0028721.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Front Wheel Speed Sensor Ring Removal</title>
            <table id="t0609048">
                <title>Special Tools</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.07*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.93*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <graphic filename="../figST1/ST1184A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="112px"
                                         scalefitheight="112px"/>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2- or 3-Jaw Puller</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <graphic filename="../figST1/ST1369A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="112px"
                                         scalefitheight="112px"/>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Hub Step Plate</para>
                                <para>ZTSE4727</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the front disc brake rotor. For additional information, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s04049_X2060318.xml" xrefid="x2060318">Front Disc Brake</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Discard the front brake anti-lock sensor ring.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use the special tools to remove the front brake anti-lock sensor ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609018" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0028720.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Front Wheel Speed Sensor Ring Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>The front brake anti-lock sensor ring must be pressed on straight.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use an appropriate size cylinder and press to install the front brake anti-lock sensor
                    ring.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0609019" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figGH1/GH1026A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the front disc brake rotor. For additional information, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s04049_X2060318.xml" xrefid="x2060318">Front Disc Brake</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Rear Wheel Speed Sensor Ring</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The rear anti-lock brake sensor indicator is attached to the differential case. It is
                        necessary to remove the ring gear in order to remove the rear anti-lock brake sensor indicator.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Refer to the appropriate section, i.e., Driveline System, Driveshaft, Rear Drive Axle,
                    or Wheel Hubs and Bearings for the procedure.
                </emph>
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
